An article in the Xinjiang Daily newspaper says authorities in Xinjiang reacted rapidly in response to the terrorist attack in Urumqi South railway station on Wednesday.
Passengers walk outside the Urumqi South Railway Station in Urumqi, capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, May 1, 2014.Â (Xinhua/Wu Zhuang)
The article says railway staff and police rushed to the scene less than one minute after the bomb was detonated. Within three minutes, the city of Urumqi started a contingency plan, with some 150 community staff and police coming to the rescue and transporting the injured to hospitals with all available vehicles. And in less than 20 minutes, all the injured were taken to hospital. Meanwhile, local police bureau immediately set up an investigation team to gather evidence, identify suspects, and investigate the case.



